;=====================================================
; MnAs crystal: data by Dillip Kumar Satapathy, Paul-Drude-Institut
; 07/2003:
; MnAs has NiAs-type lattice structure (space group #194 P6_3/mmc-D_{6h}^4)
; with 2 atoms of each type in the unit cell. This is a ferromagnetic metal
; having Tc =318 K. Above Tc it undergoes a phase transition to paramagnetic
; state involving also a structural change to a hexagonal MnP-type lattice
; structure (space group Pnma) with 2% volume reduction.
; A further structural phase transition back to the NiAs-type phase is
; observed at 398 K and it remains as paramagnetic.
;
; Another source: http://cst-www.nrl.navy.mil/lattice/struk/b8_1.html
;
; These data below are for the NiAs-type  MnAs structure below Tc.
; ------------
