;
;=======================================================================
;
;           |--------------------------|  |----------------------------|
;           |    Syngony numbers:      |  | Lattice constants required:|
;           |--------------------------|  |----------------------------|
;           |0/1= Cubic                |->| a                          |
;           | 2 = Hexagonal/Trigonal   |->| a, c                       |
;           | 3 = Tetragonal           |->| a, c                       |
;           | 4 = Trigonal/Rhombohedral|->| a, alpha                   |
;           | 5 = Orthorhombic         |->| a, b, c                    |
;           | 6 = Monoclinic           |->| a, b, c, beta              |
;           | 7 = Triclinic            |->| a, b, c, alpha, beta, gamma|
;           | 8 = ** Amorphous **      |->| ** none **                 |
;           |--------------+-----------|  |--------------------------+-|
;                          |                                         |
;|-------------------------+-----------------|                       |
;| STRUCTURE OF RECORDS:   |                 |                       |
;|-------------------------+-----------------|                       |
;|[;Comment]               |                 |                       |
;|Structure_code           |                 |                       |
;|;Comment          -------V------           |                       |
;|Nr_of_components, Syngony_number [, rho(*)]|                       |
;|[;Comment]                                 |                       |
;|Lattice_params(1-6) [, Poisson_Ratio(**)]  |skipped for Syngony=8 <+
;|;Comment                                   |
;|Name_of_Element_1 [Debye_mode,par1,par2]   |(***)
;|Nr_of_positions_of_element_1 [, Occupation]|
;|x, y, z -+                                 |
;|.......  +-coords of positions of element-1|skipped for Syngony=8;
;|x, y, z -+                                 |
;|..............................             |
;|[;Comment]                                 |
;|Name_of_Element_N [Debye_mode,par1,par2]   |(***)
;|Nr_of_positions_of_element_N [, Occupation]|
;|x, y, z -+                                 |
;|.......  + coords of positions of element-N|skipped for Syngony=8;
;|x, y, z -+                                 |
;|-------------------------------------------|
; (*)  rho           -- is the material density (gm/cm^3). This parameter
;                       is relevant Syngony_number=8 (amorphous structures)
;                       only.
; (**) Poisson_Ratio -- NOT used by X0h itself. It is simply supplied as
;                       a tabular value to calling diffraction programs.
;                       This parameter is relevant for Syngony_number=0/1
;                       (cubic structures) only.
; (***) Debye parameters must start from column 5 or later.
;       Debye_mode=1: par1=Debye factor B (in Angstrom^2),
;                     par2=temperature for B data (default=room temperature)
;       Debye_mode=2: par1=Debye Temperature,
;                     par2 not used (sample at room temperature)
;
; ----------------------------------------------------------------------
; The current limitations are:
;  1. The maximum length of Structure_code is 20 characters.
;  2. The maximum Nr_of_components=10
;  3. The maximum Nr_of_positions=20 (except for amorphous materials)
; ----------------------------------------------------------------------
; This file can contain 4 types of structures:
;
; 1. Standard or full structures -- descriptions of crystals with
;    all the necessary data for calculation of x0 and xh. The
;    examples are: Germanium, GaAs, Quartz, CsH2PO4, etc.
; 2. Uncomplete structures or templates - descriptions of crystals
;    with some parameters missing. The missing parameters must be
;    supplied by the operator. The examples are: Ge?Si?_on_Si (the
;    occupations of atomic sites for Ge and Si are required; this
;    allows to calculate x0,xh for Si/Ge solutions with different
;    Si/Ge ratio), ^A3B5-structure (the names of atoms composing the
;    structure and the unit cell parameters are required).
; 3. Crystal structures with the Nr_of_components=0 (see ~~GaN as an
;    example). These structures are used solely by X0p.exe program for
;    the calculation of Bragg angles for different reflections. Since
;    no information about chemical composition is contained, the
;    parameters x0 and xh cannot be calculated.
; 4. Amorphous materials (the structures with Syngony_number=8).
;    These are used for the calculation of x0 only. The syntax of
;    records for amorphous structures is different from that for
;    all the other structures: (a) the unit cell parameters are not
;    specified and (b) the coordinates of atoms in the unit cell
;    are not specified either. This is because there is no unit cell
;    for amorphous materials.
;    The amorphous records can be of the two types:
;    (i)  Nr_of_components#0 -- then the names of elements composing
;         the material and their Nr of positions are expected in the
;         following records (see e.g. Sapphire).
;    (ii) Nr_of_components=0 -- then the structure code is treated
;         as a chemical formula and the names of elements and their
;         Nr of positions are taken from parsing the structure code
;         (see e.g. Al2O3).
;-------------------------------------------------------------------
;
